First battle of Bull Run

July 21, 1861

Three months after the attack on Fort Sumter, the Union scouts discovered an important concentration of Confederated troops just 40 Km. to Washington. Scaried about the real danger, president Licoln sent a quickly created force under the general McDowell. Well informed by the infiltrated spies in Washington, the Confederacy could sent 10,000 troops under the general J.E. Johnston as reinforcements for the James Longstreet's men near the Manasas Junction. The first battle of the war was underway.

